snippet.textDisplay: Funny yet unfortunate story. I got to attend a lecture given by Jullian Foddy who worked on the VFX for this film, and they showed off an in-progress version of the final New York web-slinging sequence. It was cool to see some of the ideas they had that were removed however the worst part about it was that it used the full version of the homecoming re-imagining of the classic Spider-man theme. It was SO GOOD yet the final film goes with their own unique yet less memorable Spider-man theme. Seeing that sequence with the classic theme orchestrated with subtle uses of guitars was way more satisfying that what we got.

snippet.textDisplay:
My interpretation of the customs lady was that Spider-Man operates in New York and simply isn't that widely known outside of that area. Let alone outside of the US.


As for the german dub, the animated series actually had people refer to Spider-Man as "Spinne". Not sure what was up with that, especially since the title doesn't translate the name.


And honestly, some people belittle those who thought Mysterio might be a hero, but while I did know he was a villain in the comics, so was Mordo, and he doesn't go bad until the end of that movie. So I totally would've believed that Mysterio starts out as a hero and only becomes the antagonist after something else happens. Same thing with Gwen's death in TASM. Everyone who read the comics knew about it, but many were still wondering if the movie would ACTUALLY do it or change Gwen's fate.

snippet.textDisplay:
You might want to edit the video because the point where he talks about the stealth suit bunching up around the old web shooter he wasn't talking about his web shooters. It was a reference to the elevator scene in Spiderman 2 when Spidey lost his powers and was complimented on his spiderman suit. His response was "thanks. It bunches up in the crotch a bit though"

What annoys me about the complaints about the lack of a spider sense in the films is the fact that spider sense doesn't have a physical manifestation. I thought the way they handle spider sense in Civil War was perfect, at the time. It was obvious if you knew what to look for. Fair enough, in Homecoming it wasn't so obvious, and the inclusion of hairs standing on end in Infinity War, in my eyes, was just the writers including it to please the whiners. Far From Home could have been better if it didn't cater so much to those people, but that's not to say it wasn't a great film. It's easily one of my favourites of the entire MCU. And I never doubted that Mysterio was the bad guy, not even for a second, lol

as much as I love JK Simmons as JJJ, Peter is a MINOR.

Will this be explored, or will they just keep f*cking the kid?
I understand that there are so many interesting ways to explore the consequences of his actions, but that doesn’t excuse a whole ass adult endangering a literal CHILD by helping to expose his identity.
